                    Office of Plan and Provider Relations

   The Department of Managed Health Care's Office of Plan and Provider
   Relations is designed to open the lines of communication with health
   plans, hospitals, physicians and other providers to assure early
   intervention for the resolution of consumer issues. We identify
   systemic problems and issues with the managed care system and work with
   the plans and providers to resolve these concerns.

   This site provides health plan representatives and providers with
   access to Department communications and other information. Please
   contact us with any questions or suggestions for this office.
   Enrollee Grievance Assistance
   ___________________________________________________________________

   If you are a provider seeking to assist an individual enrollee in a
   grievance with a health plan, please click on the following link:
   Consumer Complaint Process
   Items of Interest to Health Plans
   ___________________________________________________________________

   If you are a representative of a health plan or other interested party,
   the Department has gathered a few items that may be of interest to you
   at the link below:
   Items of Interest to Health Plans
   Financial Solvency Reporting
   ___________________________________________________________________

   If you would like information about the reporting requirements for
   health plans and providers who accept financial risk from plans, please
   click on the following link:
   Financial Solvency Reporting Requirements
   Payment Difficulties
   ___________________________________________________________________

   If you are a provider who is experiencing difficulties obtaining
   payment from a health plan or a delegated medical group or independent
   practice association, please click on the following link:
   Handling Payment Problems
   The Law
   ___________________________________________________________________

   If you would like to see the text of the laws (statutes and
   regulations) that the Department uses to regulate health plans, follow
   the relevant link:
   Statutes Pertaining to Health Plans Regulations Pertaining to Health
   Plans
   If you are interested in following legislation related to managed
   health care that is currently before the State Legislature, click the
   following link to the Department's Library:
   Pending Legislation
   For information on pending regulations that the Department is currently
   considering, click on the following link:
   Pending Regulations
   Committees and Boards
   ___________________________________________________________________

   Various boards and committees advise the Department to ensure that the
   voices of everyone affected by managed health care are heard. To access
   schedules, agendas and other information related to the Department's
   boards and committees, please click on the following link:
   Advisory Boards and Committees
